  "text": "The interactions between cells and their surrounding extracellular matrices (ECMs) play a crucial role in normal physiological processes such as tissue development, morphogenesis and cellular differentiation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Abnormal changes in cell and ECM interaction have been shown to cause diverse pathological conditions, including tissue fibrosis and tumor associated stromagenesis [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
